Subject: =?UTF-8?q?feat(slayzone):=20in-pane=20window.open=20popups=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=86=92=20pane=20tab=20(NEW=5FPOPUP,=20OAuth)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 2 of in-pane new-window adoption. A windowless task Browser has no OS
window to host a popup; a sized window.open (with window features, e.g. an OAuth
flow) requests NEW_POPUP → a separate visible Browser (a stray window, or a
shell-takeover recursion). Convert NEW_POPUP → NEW_BACKGROUND_TAB for embedded-tab
(task) Browsers in Browser::AddNewContents (mirrors the existing Mac-fullscreen
popup→tab conversion) → the popup becomes a background tab that the
TabStripModelObserver (patch 0076) adopts into the task's pane.

Background, NOT foreground: a foreground tab would become the hidden Browser's
active tab and trap its RWHV in the never-shown BrowserView (blank pane); content
tabs must stay background so our slot composites them. The renderer foregrounds
the new PANE tab itself on OnNewView.

Verified via CDP: a sized window.open adds a pane tile (no stray window).
---
 chrome/browser/ui/browser.cc | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/chrome/browser/ui/browser.cc b/chrome/browser/ui/browser.cc
index 8f8852b2af1ac..db4cbba03bd15 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/ui/browser.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/ui/browser.cc
@@ -97,6 +97,7 @@
 #include "chrome/browser/ui/browser_command_controller.h"
 #include "chrome/browser/ui/browser_commands.h"
 #include "chrome/browser/ui/browser_finder.h"
+#include "chrome/browser/slayzone/layout_features.h"
 #include "chrome/browser/ui/browser_list.h"
 #include "chrome/browser/ui/browser_live_tab_context.h"
 #include "chrome/browser/ui/browser_manager_service.h"
@@ -2070,6 +2071,20 @@ content::WebContents* Browser::AddNewContents(
     const blink::mojom::WindowFeatures& window_features,
     bool user_gesture,
     bool* was_blocked) {
+  // SlayZone: a windowless embedded-tab (task) Browser has no OS window to host
+  // a popup, and we want page-opened popups (window.open with features, OAuth)
+  // to become pane TABS — adopted into the task's pane by the
+  // SlayzoneEmbeddedTabHost TabStripModelObserver — rather than a stray window
+  // (or a shell-takeover recursion). Convert to a BACKGROUND tab (not
+  // foreground): a foreground tab would become the hidden Browser's active tab,
+  // trapping its RWHV in the never-shown BrowserView (blank pane); content tabs
+  // must stay background so our slot is free to composite them. The renderer
+  // foregrounds the new PANE tab itself on OnNewView.
+  if (slayzone::IsEmbeddedTabBrowser(this) &&
+      disposition == WindowOpenDisposition::NEW_POPUP) {
+    disposition = WindowOpenDisposition::NEW_BACKGROUND_TAB;
+  }
+
   FullscreenController* fullscreen_controller = browser_window_features()
                                                     ->exclusive_access_manager()
                                                     ->fullscreen_controller();
